The paper deals with the problem of handling multiple tables in datasets, which is a common issue in database systems (cs.DB). The focus of the paper is on machine learning models, specifically decision trees and SVMs, which are popular in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves simulation-based analyses and theoretical research, which are relevant to the fields of data science (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
